Interface Summary
TreeNodeVisitor Instances of TreeNodeVisitor are supplied to TreeTraverser objects.
 

Class Summary
BinaryTree<K extends Comparable<K>,V> A data structure consisting of nodes that can each have either zero, one, or at most, two children (child nodes).
LinkedList<E> Implementation of a doubly-linked list.
ListNode<E> Represents a node (or entry) in a LinkedList.
Queue<E> The Queue class implements a first-in first-out (FIFO) data structure.
Stack<E> The Stack class implements a last-in first-out (LIFO) data structure.
TestDataStructures  
TreeNode<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V> Represents a node in a BinaryTree.
TreeTraverser Traverses a BinaryTree in either pre-, in- or post-order fashion.
 

Exception Summary
NoSuchKeyException Thrown to indicate that a key-value mapping was not found in a BinaryTree.
QueueEmptyException Thrown to indicate that peek() or dequeue() was invoked on an empty Queue.
StackEmptyException Thrown to indicate that peek() or push() was invoked on an empty Stack
